# Tor configuration for Bybit API access with SOCKS5 proxy
# Optimized for cryptocurrency trading platforms

## Basic Tor Configuration
SocksPort 9050
ControlPort 9051
CookieAuthentication 1
CookieAuthFile tor_control_cookie

## Network Configuration
# Exit nodes in regions with better crypto exchange access
ExitNodes {us},{ca},{gb},{de},{nl},{sg},{jp}
StrictNodes 1

## Connection Optimization
# Reduce timeouts for trading applications
CircuitBuildTimeout 30
CircuitIdleTimeout 300
NewCircuitPeriod 60

# Connection limits
MaxClientCircuitsPending 48
NumCPUs 4

## SOCKS5 Configuration
# Allow SOCKS5 connections
SocksPolicy accept *
SocksPort 9050 IsolateDestAddr IsolateDestPort

## DNS Configuration
# Use Tor's DNS resolver
DNSPort 5353
AutomapHostsOnResolve 1
AutomapHostsSuffixes .exit,.onion

## Performance Tuning
# Bandwidth limits (adjust based on your connection)
RelayBandwidthRate 1000 KB
RelayBandwidthBurst 2000 KB

# Keepalive settings
KeepalivePeriod 600

## Security Settings
# Disable potentially problematic features
UseEntryGuards 1
NumEntryGuards 3

## Logging
Log notice file tor_notice.log
Log info file tor_info.log

## Directory Configuration
DataDirectory tor_data

## Bridge Configuration (if needed)
# Uncomment and add bridges if direct connection fails
#Bridge obfs4 1.2.3.4:1234 ABCDEF1234567890 cert=ABCDEFGHIJKLM+123456 iat-mode=0
#UseBridges 1

## Specific for Bybit API
# Create dedicated circuits for Bybit domains
LongLivedPorts 443
CircuitStreamTimeout 60
